@startuml
title MicroMeet - Activity Diagram (Send Update Notifications)

start
:1. Scheduler triggers notification job;
:2. System starts notification processing;
:3. System finds meetups with updates;

if (Any updated meetups?) then (Yes)
  :4. For each updated meetup, gather recipients;
  :5. Read participant list;
  :6. Compose notification message;
  :7. Deliver notification via gateway;
  :8. Record success/failure;
  :9. Count sent notifications;
  :10. Log job result (sentCount);
else (No)
  :11. Log "No updates to notify";
endif

stop

legend bottom
Steps mapping (numbers match actions):
1 Trigger scheduler job
2 Start processing
3 Find updated meetups
4 Gather recipients (loop)
5 Read participant list
6 Compose notification
7 Deliver via gateway
8 Record result
9 Count sent notifications
10 Log job result
11 Log no-updates case
endlegend

@enduml